5:{s:4:"data";s:1387:"<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>I think there’s a difference between having a bestselling book–meaning through marketing, PR and buying that first wave of customers–and writing a bestselling book. The second implies that the product propels itself to the best seller list. That’s not to say that I’m Tolstoy or the best writer, but I used Facebook and Twitter more for feed back as I was creating and refining the book than for the actual marketing itself. My main online tool for priming the pump for the launch of the book was the blog. That was the heartbeat and the nexus for all the different tools that I use.</p></blockquote></div>\n<p>Via <a href="http://blogs.forbes.com/stevenbertoni/2011/04/14/tim-ferriss-on-facebook-twitter-and-building-a-huge-web-brand/">Tim Ferriss On Facebook, Twitter And Building A Huge Web Brand &#8211; Steven Bertoni &#8211; Money Talks &#8211; Forbes</a>. I also liked this quote:</p>\n<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>SB: How can a magazine catch up to the Web?</p>\n<p>TF: If I worked for a magazine that’s very behind the times, I wouldn’t reinvent the wheel. I’d use WordPress as a content management system which has very good SEO out of the box. Companies spend so much time trying to develop something proprietary it’s ridiculous–you have thousands of people already working on WordPress.</p></blockquote></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 17:32:37 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Matt";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:37;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"WPCandy: WordCamp Atlanta 2011 date moves to the fall";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/SvUsP_3sxZI/wordcamp-atlanta-2011-date-moves-to-the-fall";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2257:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17017" title="WordCamp Atlanta 2011 logo (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wordcampatlantalogo-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="239" /></a></p><p>WordCamp Atlanta 2011 was <a title="WordCamp Atlanta is officially scheduled for May 6th and 7th" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/wordcamp-atlanta-2011-may-6-7">initially scheduled</a> for the beginning of May. Due to the organization team wanting to ensure a larger event than 2010, the event has been pushed back to a yet-to-be announced date this fall.</p><p>Not much was said in the <a title="WordCamp Atlanta date announcement" href="http://atlantawordcamp.com/2011/04/update-wordcamp-atlanta-2011-is-moving-to-fall-2011/">announcement</a>, but organizer Tessa Horehled did share some of their plans for the extra time before this year&#8217;s event:</p><blockquote><p>This year’s event is going to be pushed back to Fall so we can ensure this year’s event even bigger and better than last year, by bringing more great leaders from the Atlanta WordCamp community into the fold and securing a brand new venue which we hope to announce in the coming months.</p></blockquote><p>We&#8217;ll keep an eye out and notify you when WordCamp Atlanta 2011&#8242;s date is firmed up. Until then, who&#8217;s looking forward to the next event in Atlanta?</p><p>I attended last year&#8217;s event, which was fantastic, and <a title="Parent/child theme presentation on Slideshare" href="http://www.slideshare.net/ryanimel/speeding-up-site-development-with-parent-and-child-themes">presented on child themes</a>. I&#8217;m looking forward to attending this year, though I will probably be more focused on <a title="WPCandy covers WordCamps" href="http://wpcandy.com/on/wordcamp">covering WordCamp</a> than I will be trying to present on a particular topic. Who has attended in the past that will be going again this year?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016">WordCamp Atlanta 2011 date moves to the fall </a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 16:43:10 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:38;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 4/15";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9891";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/558Z0QN3q9I/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:745:"<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9892" title="diesel" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/diesel.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="87" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://stockable.net/diesel/"><strong>Diesel</strong></a> is a dark theme designed for video game blogs.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9893" title="leathernote" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/leathernote.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/themes/leathernote"><strong>LeatherNote</strong></a> is a sleek leather notepad design for WordPress.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/558Z0QN3q9I" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 13:00:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:39;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress and the Uneditable Theme Templates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9886";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/h3F09z24nqg/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1238:"<p>So, you have a plugin requiring that you make a change to one of your <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a> theme templates, or you just want move something around in your theme or alter your CSS. You&#8217;ve arrived at Appearance -&gt; Editor as instructed, but there&#8217;s no &#8220;Update File&#8221; button.</p>\n<p>This is unfortunately another one of those common annoyances related to your hosting provider&#8217;s server configuration that can take you off guard and lead to plenty of confusion. Fortunately, it&#8217;s easy to fix (or work around).</p>\n<p>Try <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Changing_File_Permissions">changing the permissions</a> of the theme files that you want to edit to 666. If that doesn&#8217;t work, just use an <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/FTP_Clients">FTP or SFTP client</a> and a <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#Text_editor">plain text editor</a> to edit them remotely.</p>\n<p>Of course, if neither of those methods are working out for you, please stop by the <a href="http://wordpress.org/support/">WordPress Support Forums</a> for further assistance.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/h3F09z24nqg" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 14 Apr 2011 13:00:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:40;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"WPCandy: Vote here: Theme Madness 2011, Round 1 Day 4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16999";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/0yJsIsdLAfc/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-4-voting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14790:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16999"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17000" title="Theme Madness Round 1 Day 4 voting (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/thememadnessround1day4voting-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>This week we will be running through Round 1 of <a title="Theme Madness 2011" href="http://wpcandy.com/series-on/theme-madness-2011">Theme Madness</a>, with eight games happening each day. In fact, today is the last day of Round 1 voting. Today’s games will be:</p><ul><li><a href="http://www.dev4press.com/">Dev4Press</a> vs. <a href="http://www.indonez.com/">Indonez</a></li><li><a href="http://tokokoo.com/">Tokokoo</a> vs. <a href="http://standardtheme.com/">Standard Theme</a></li><li><a href="http://www.pagelines.com/">Pagelines</a> vs. <a href="http://wonderthemes.com/">Wonder Themes</a></li><li><a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://themewarrior.com/">ThemeWarrior</a></li><li><a href="http://gorillathemes.com/">Gorilla Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://wpshower.com/">WPShower</a></li><li><a href="http://thethemefoundry.com/">The Theme Foundry</a> vs. <a href="http://themefuse.com/">ThemeFuse</a></li><li><a href="http://www.wpzoom.com/">WPZoom</a> vs. <a href="http://www.vivathemes.com/">Viva Themes</a></li><li><a href="http://diythemes.com/">DIYThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-force.com/">ThemeForce</a></li></ul><p>All of the polls and instructions can be found just after the jump, so be sure to click through to have your voice heard. Voting will take place for the next 48 hours, and close at midnight on the 15th (Eastern Standard Time).</p><p>If you need a reminder, the rules can be found <a title="How to win your Theme Madness 2011 Trophy" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-rules">here</a>. Good luck to everyone playing!</p><p><span id="more-16999"></span></p><h3>Dev4Press vs. Indonez</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915034"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915034"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915034/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">Market Research</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Dev4Press on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/milangd">@MilanGD</a> or <a title="Indonez on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/indoneztheme">@IndonezTheme</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Dev4Press or Indonez start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Tokokoo vs. Standard Theme</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915051"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915051"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915051/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online surveys</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</stro