INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (285, 1, '2011-02-24 10:35:14', '2011-02-24 10:35:14', '<img class="alignnone" title="iris" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Eye_iris.jpg" alt="" width="703" height="470" />\r\n\r\nAniridia is characterized by complete or partial absence of the iris. Pax6, which is responsible for eye development, does not function correctly and disrupt the iris development in the fetus. There are many variations of aniridia that range from mild to severe. Depending on what other conditions affected the eyes, visual acuity may remain relatively unimpaired or greatly reduced.\r\n\r\nAniridia is a very rare disease and seen in 1 of 64,000 -96,000 live births. Since it is inherited as an autosomal-dominant trait, each child born to an affected parent will have a 50% chance of having the gene. However, the expression of the gene may vary within families as well as between families. Affected individuals usually show little variability between the two eyes (bilateral). 2/3of all cases come with a family history. Aniridia also occurs in sporadic form, which means the child does not have a family history of the disease. This counts for 1/3 of cases.', 'What is Aniridia?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '251-revision-9', '', '', '2011-02-24 10:35:14', '2011-02-24 10:35:14', '', 251, 'http://web3.cmmt.ubc.ca/dev/uncategorized/251-revision-9/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
