INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (359, 1, '2011-02-27 00:10:41', '2011-02-27 00:10:41', 'Children with aniridia typically have about 20/100 vision, but this varies between individuals. They need to be carefully followed by an ophthalmologist throughout life, so complication can be diagnosed and promptly treated. Vision typically gets worse with age as cataracts progress though these can be treated with surgery and contact lenses. Glaucoma frequently develops and affect the function of optic nerve, further reducing vision. Ongoing screening for Wilm’s tumor is important. With careful treatment and assistance for adapting to living with reduced vision, children with aniridia will have a very good outcome.\r\n\r\nIt has been suggested that gene therapy may improve several of the clinical defects. If the affected individuals are identified by prenatal diagnosis, partial therapeutic correction of the lens is possible by gene therapy.\r\n\r\nMost children with aniridia will have normal intelligence, and it is important to build children’s self-esteem and independence. This is essential for them to fully participate in life activities with low vision that might gradually progress to blindness. Genetic counselling can help parents to learn about the disorder itself and what to be expected in order to cope with the condition.', 'What are some treatments and outcomes?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '260-revision-4', '', '', '2011-02-27 00:10:41', '2011-02-27 00:10:41', '', 260, 'http://web3.cmmt.ubc.ca/dev/uncategorized/260-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
